    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 11th with a clear top-tier anchor in **Trea Turner** (72.23), whose elite speed profile perfectly aligns with the slow delivery of Pfaadt. **Trea Turner** leads our daily rankings, bolstered by his lead-off spot and favorable R/SB potential. Joining him at the top of the board is **Yordan Alvarez** (68.04), whose raw power remains matchup-proof despite a moderate xERA from Castillo, and **Kyle Schwarber** (65.95), who benefits from a favorable park factor and high xwOBA against the Pfaadt matchup. **Colt Keith** (63.90) and **Logan O'Hoppe** (62.94) also grade out as strong starts today; **Colt Keith** thrives in the favorable matchup against Junk, while **Logan O'Hoppe** capitalizes on Williamson\u2019s high xERA (5.28) to provide high-efficiency output from the bottom of the order.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Carson Benge** (39.27), who fell just shy of our 40.0 floor. While **Carson Benge** offers versatility, the left-on-left disadvantage against Lopez, J significantly handicapped his efficiency, ultimately keeping him relegated to the bench. Similarly, we are monitoring **Victor Scott II** (35.34); despite his elite speed\u2014a priority for the Zebras\u2014the combination of a tough matchup against Suarez and a bottom-tier batting order position makes him a liability for today\u2019s cap-constrained strategy. We remain cautious with **Christian Yelich** (40.19) and **Josh Smith** (40.06), both of whom are hovering precariously above our bench threshold; their starts are contingent on their platoon edges and order placement, but they remain high-risk plays against Griffin and Sheehan respectively. Owners should note that **Yordan Alvarez** remains a pending lineup risk, and **Kazuma Okamoto** and **Zac Veen** continue to be unavailable for active duty as they navigate IL/Minors status. We have no active exposure to **Lars Nootbaar**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, or **Luis Pena** today.",
